RT-qPCR was used to quantify the PEDV SH present in the feces and intestinal tissues of challenged piglets. In feces, viral load reached the highest level at 2 d.p.i, then declined somewhat at 3 d.p.i. It should be noted that 2 challenged piglets died on 3 d.p.i. (Fig. 6
). PEDV in the tissues of the duodenum, jejunum, and ileum were quantified. The greater viral load was shown in the jejuna and the ilea (Table 4
). No viral RNA was detected in the feces or the intestine tissues of the uninfected piglets.
